{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":710,"text":"Take a look at this drawing."},{"time":2579,"text":"Can you tell what it is?"},{"time":4183,"text":"I'm a molecular biologist by training,"},{"time":6930,"text":"and I've seen a lot of these kinds of drawings."},{"time":9533,"text":"They're usually referred to as a model figure,"},{"time":12625,"text":"a drawing that shows how we think"},{"time":14359,"text":"a cellular or molecular process occurs."},{"time":17023,"text":"This particular drawing is of a process"},{"time":19522,"text":"called clathrin-mediated endocytosis."},{"time":23845,"text":"It's a process by which a molecule can get"},{"time":26455,"text":"from the outside of the cell to the inside"},{"time":28693,"text":"by getting captured in a bubble or a vesicle"},{"time":31230,"text":"that then gets internalized by the cell."},{"time":34050,"text":"There's a problem with this drawing, though,"},{"time":35885,"text":"and it's mainly in what it doesn't show."},{"time":38517,"text":"From lots of experiments,"},{"time":39982,"text":"from lots of different scientists,"},{"time":41817,"text":"we know a lot about what these molecules look like,"},{"time":44813,"text":"how they move around in the cell,"},{"time":46495,"text":"and that this is all taking place"},{"time":48320,"text":"in an incredibly dynamic environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51310,"text":"So in collaboration with a clathrin\nexpert Tomas Kirchhausen,"},{"time":54783,"text":"we decided to create a new kind of model figure"},{"time":57102,"text":"that showed all of that."},{"time":59126,"text":"So we start outside of the cell."},{"time":60862,"text":"Now we're looking inside."},{"time":62510,"text":"Clathrin are these three-legged molecules"},{"time":64590,"text":"that can self-assemble into soccer-ball-like shapes."},{"time":67878,"text":"Through connections with a membrane,"},{"time":69575,"text":"clathrin is able to deform the membrane"},{"time":71742,"text":"and form this sort of a cup"},{"time":73155,"text":"that forms this sort of a bubble, or a vesicle,"},{"time":75462,"text":"that's now capturing some of the proteins"},{"time":77246,"text":"that were outside of the cell."},{"time":78900,"text":"Proteins are coming in now that\nbasically pinch off this vesicle,"},{"time":82398,"text":"making it separate from the rest of the membrane,"},{"time":84982,"text":"and now clathrin is basically done with its job,"},{"time":87374,"text":"and so proteins are coming in now —"},{"time":88612,"text":"we've covered them yellow and orange —"},{"time":90558,"text":"that are responsible for taking\napart this clathrin cage."},{"time":93100,"text":"And so all of these proteins\ncan get basically recycled"},{"time":96382,"text":"and used all over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97918,"text":"These processes are too small to be seen directly,"},{"time":101327,"text":"even with the best microscopes,"},{"time":103159,"text":"so animations like this provide a really powerful way"},{"time":105790,"text":"of visualizing a hypothesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108808,"text":"Here's another illustration,"},{"time":110654,"text":"and this is a drawing of how a researcher might think"},{"time":113390,"text":"that the HIV virus gets into and out of cells."},{"time":116895,"text":"And again, this is a vast oversimplification"},{"time":119414,"text":"and doesn't begin to show"},{"time":121158,"text":"what we actually know about these processes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123640,"text":"You might be surprised to know"},{"time":125855,"text":"that these simple drawings are the only way"},{"time":128622,"text":"that most biologists visualize\ntheir molecular hypotheses."},{"time":132454,"text":"Why?"},{"time":133482,"text":"Because creating movies of processes"},{"time":135472,"text":"as we think they actually occur is really hard."},{"time":138486,"text":"I spent months in Hollywood\nlearning 3D animation software,"},{"time":142119,"text":"and I spend months on each animation,"},{"time":144400,"text":"and that's just time that most\nresearchers can't afford."},{"time":147750,"text":"The payoffs can be huge, though."},{"time":149950,"text":"Molecular animations are unparalleled"},{"time":152334,"text":"in their ability to convey a great deal of information"},{"time":155775,"text":"to broad audiences with extreme accuracy."},{"time":159367,"text":"And I'm working on a new project now"},{"time":160870,"text":"called \"The Science of HIV\""},{"time":162308,"text":"where I'll be animating the entire life cycle"},{"time":164670,"text":"of the HIV virus as accurately as possible"},{"time":167774,"text":"and all in molecular detail."},{"time":169735,"text":"The animation will feature data"},{"time":171886,"text":"from thousands of researchers\ncollected over decades,"},{"time":174862,"text":"data on what this virus looks like,"},{"time":177942,"text":"how it's able to infect cells in our body,"},{"time":181030,"text":"and how therapeutics are\nhelping to combat infection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185002,"text":"Over the years, I found that animations"},{"time":187331,"text":"aren't just useful for communicating an idea,"},{"time":190150,"text":"but they're also really useful"},{"time":191646,"text":"for exploring a hypothesis."},{"time":193958,"text":"Biologists for the most part are\nstill using a paper and pencil"},{"time":197152,"text":"to visualize the processes they study,"},{"time":199374,"text":"and with the data we have now,\nthat's just not good enough anymore."},{"time":202854,"text":"The process of creating an animation"},{"time":205270,"text":"can act as a catalyst that allows researchers"},{"time":207927,"text":"to crystalize and refine their own ideas."},{"time":210878,"text":"One researcher I worked with"},{"time":212662,"text":"who works on the molecular mechanisms"},{"time":214438,"text":"of neurodegenerative diseases"},{"time":216222,"text":"came up with experiments that were related"},{"time":218200,"text":"directly to the animation that\nshe and I worked on together,"},{"time":221183,"text":"and in this way, animation can\nfeed back into the research process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225304,"text":"I believe that animation can change biology."},{"time":228157,"text":"It can change the way that we\ncommunicate with one another,"},{"time":230725,"text":"how we explore our data"},{"time":232348,"text":"and how we teach our students."},{"time":233675,"text":"But for that change to happen,"},{"time":235129,"text":"we need more researchers creating animations,"},{"time":238286,"text":"and toward that end, I brought together a team"},{"time":240541,"text":"of biologists, animators and programmers"},{"time":243678,"text":"to create a new, free, open-source software —"},{"time":246725,"text":"we call it Molecular Flipbook —"},{"time":248629,"text":"that's created just for biologists"},{"time":250525,"text":"just to create molecular animations."},{"time":254070,"text":"From our testing, we've found\nthat it only takes 15 minutes"},{"time":257782,"text":"for a biologist who has never\ntouched animation software before"},{"time":261050,"text":"to create her first molecular animation"},{"time":263786,"text":"of her own hypothesis."},{"time":265308,"text":"We're also building an online database"},{"time":267458,"text":"where anyone can view, download and contribute"},{"time":270233,"text":"their own animations."},{"time":271849,"text":"We're really excited to announce"},{"time":273820,"text":"that the beta version of the molecular animation"},{"time":276282,"text":"software toolkit will be available for download today."},{"time":280490,"text":"We are really excited to see\nwhat biologists will create with it"},{"time":283233,"text":"and what new insights they're able to gain"},{"time":285289,"text":"from finally being able to animate"},{"time":286770,"text":"their own model figures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288473,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290713,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}